(31, '<img src="uploads/neeraj/projectnotesPic/2015-01-09_07:13:02pm_pcrf.png.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> Technology support for Mobile Network operators from OEM like Ericsson, NSN, Huawie, Cisco etc. have come a long way from only providing only circuit switched telephony to providing Smart Service Aware Charging Control. <s><br/> <s>3GPP a standardization body for telecom services in 2008 in its release 8 standardized a technology for Policy and Charging Rules Function(PCRF) and Policy and Charging Enforcement Function (PCEF), although the standards are quite vast to explain here and may be out of scope, at this point of time consider that PCRF and PCEF function in a server-client relationship over diameter protocol. PCRF acts as a Diameter Server and PCEF as Client. <br/> <s>The PCRF based on subscribers profile passes a set of rules to the PCEF which applies to these rules to all services. The PCEF has a Packet Inspection and Service Classification engine, which looks into every packet passing from the service provider<r>s network to the Internet and visa-versa. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The Packet Inspection and Service Classification Engine has three types of Packet Inspection Rules <s><br/> <s>1. Shallow Inspection: Layer 3 and Layer 4 of the packet means the IP addresses of the sender and receiver and the port number which tell us about the service like http, https, ftp, rtsp, rtp etc. <br/> <s>2. Deep Inspection: Layer 7 headers and text based search on the pakets. The PCEF looks at the L7 headers like URI, Http method, Host-Server etc and text based rules. <br/> <s>3. Heuristic Analysis: Based on the pattern of flow of IP packets the service being used can be judged with high probability. A lot of traffic can be judged using Heuristic Analysis of packets like torrent, VoIP, Skype, Wiber etc. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Now based on these rules the traffic is classified, relevant QoS can be applied and charged accordingly.');
