is the solution? How much risk-taking or innovation was involved? <s><br/> <s>Â 2. Usefulness: Does the solution solve a real problem? Is it a good candidate for incubation? <s><br/> <s>Â 3. Relevance: How relevant is the hack to Science or Science portfolio companies? <s><br/> <s>Â For more info: http://goo.gl/WHxPzo'),
(52, '<img src="uploads/shruti/projectnotesPic/2015-01-13_01:32:23pm_Screenshot from 2015-01-13 18:56:12.png.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> <s> <br/> <s>Â 09:00, Sat, 17 Jan 2015 - Till 19 Jan <s><br/> <s>Â MG Road , Central Bangalore India <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â Event Description: Â Knowlarity API Hackathon invites all techies to come and build awesome applications on the Knowlarity API. Interact with the very team that built the API, get to know all you need to and let your imagination go wild ! <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â All you need is familiarity with HTML, CSS, Javascript, MySQL <a>amp; Python. Show the best you can do, and find a chance to work with Knowlarity for full-time. Additional cool prizes are there, register at http://www.venturesity.com/companies-knowlarity and be updated. <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â About Knowlarity: Knowlarity is Indiaâ€™s largest cloud telephony company. Funded by Sequoia Capital and Mayfield, it has grown by leaps and bounds since their inception in 2009, powering more than 8,000 companies in India and abroad. They have a presence in 65 countries with headquarter in Singapore. To know more visit http://www.knowlarity.com/ <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â Prizes to be won: <s><br/> <s>Â  Â  Best Team <s><br/> <s>Â  Â  Best Startup Idea <s><br/> <s>Â  Â  Best Individual Developer <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> http://www.venturesity.com/knowlarity-api-hackathon.html'),
(53, '<img src="uploads/shruti/projectnotesPic/2015-01-13_01:41:39pm_stayzilla.png.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/>  <br/> <s>10:00, Sat, 31 Jan 2015 - Till 01 Feb <br/> <s>Stayzilla office , South Bangalore India <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Event Description: Venturesity invites all techies to the Stayzilla Hackathon, and hack to turn data into an awesome product. All you need to do is apply, attend and code. In this 24 hours of coding, showcase what you have built and get hired. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>About Venturesity: Venturesity is a platform to connect <s>right talent to the right company via challenges hence defining the future of recruitment. <s>To know more visit http://www.venturesity.com/ <br/> <s> <br/> <s>About Stayzilla: Stayzilla is an online platform that enables individuals to research and reserve value hotels across India. Stayzilla is one of India<r>s fastest growing start-ups in the travel industry, and is led by a visionary founder and backed by some of India<r>s best-known investors. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Find all details at: http://www.venturesity.com/stayzilla-data-to-product-hackathon.html'),
(54, '<img src="uploads/neeraj/projectnotesPic/2015-01-13_01:53:54pm_isro.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> An ISRO-developed low-cost technology which protects PSLV fuel tanks from flames can now be used to safeguard railway coaches, buildings and vehicles from catching fire. According to the Indian Space Research Organization (ISRO), the new compound, christened CASPOL, is a water-based ready-to-coat and easy-to-use flameproof coating, with excellent flame retardant, waterproofing and thermal control properties. <a>quot;It can be applied on walls, clothes, paper, thatched roofs and wood to protect them from fire,<a>quot; the space agency said Monday in a statement. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>CASPOL, which contains no toxic materials, is eco-friendly. <a>quot;The emulsion can be sprayed or spread using a brush on surfaces that need fire protection. One litre of CASPOL can coat 1.5 sq metre with a thickness of 500 micron, which is practically adequate for fire protection and thermal insulation,<a>quot; the statement said. It can also be used as a flame retardant material in railways and automobiles where the seat cushions can be made flameproof without affecting the cushioning characteristics. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Shopping malls and theatres can be easily rendered fire resistant by using CASPOL in their seat cushions and walls. CASPOL can also be applied over the concrete surfaces of buildings to prevent water seeping as its application fills micro cracks and holes effectively. It also helps keep building cooler by at least five to six degrees Celsius. ISRO is presently looking for a suitable industry partner to commercialize this technology for social benefit. <s><br/> <s> <br/> <s>Reffer:http://news.siliconindia.com/technology/ISRO-Technology-For-Fire-Resistant-Houses-Automobiles-nid-177554-cid-2.html?utm_campaign=Newsletter<a>amp;utm_medium=Email<a>amp;utm_source=r1indiacom'),
(55, '<img src="uploads/neeraj/projectnotesPic/2015-01-13_01:55:30pm_storedot-590x330.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> An Israeli start-up StoreDot has developed ultra-fast chargers that can charge smartphone batteries in two minutes flat. The batteries, shown at the <a>quot;Consumer Electronics Show<a>quot; in Las Vegas recently, have slightly shorter lives but can still last about five hours on a two-minute charge. <a>quot;But given how quick the batteries take to recharge, doing so a couple of times a day shouldn<r>t be a problem,<a>quot; the company said in a statement. <br/> <s> <br/> <s> <br/> <s>During a demonstration, the firm also showed that the bio-organic charger system which they are developing at the lab in Tel Aviv can finally recharge a smartphone battery in just 30 seconds. <a>quot;It was created by using re-building battery technology from the bottom up,<a>quot; Doron Myersdorf, the company<r>s CEO, was quoted as saying in a BBC report. The reactions that happen in the battery are entirely different from those in normal ones, and include specially synthesised organic molecules.'),
(56, '<img src="uploads/neeraj/projectnotesPic/2015-01-13_01:57:11pm_hike_acquires_zip_phone.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> Indian chat application firm Hike Messenger has acquired US-based voice-calling company Zip Phone, it said in a statement. The acquisition is aimed at expanding Hike`s product range in the internet-based communication space, the company said, declining to disclose the acquisition sum. <br/> <s> <br/> <s> <br/> <s><a>quot;Zip Phone`s technology will allow us to bring free voice calling to the market much faster. Incidentally, this is one of the top requested features from our users as well,<a>quot; Kavin Bharti Mittal, founder and chief executive officer, Hike Messenger said. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Zip Phone, a one-man startup founded by Anuj Jain in the US, has developed a voice-calling app that works globally. Launched in December 2012, Hike has over 35 million users and has raised $86 million from Tiger Global and BSB till date. '),
(57, '<img src="uploads/neeraj/projectnotesPic/2015-01-13_01:59:16pm_xiaomi-phones.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> Xiaomi the leading Chinese mobile maker led by its charismatic founder Lei Jun, was 2014s news maker for all the good reasons and going with that, he also disclosed his view very publicly declaring domination on the world market, on an international press conference. Cited his view of taking the world market in the coming 10 years and dominate the others governing the market reports, Techradar. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>His view can take a possible shape in regards to its present position as third leading smart phone vendor, just behind the two giants Apple and Samsung, which in future may be over passed. To attain this position Xiaomi initially left behind Hi-end range to concentrate on the mid range and budget phones. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>For this year this upcoming giant has made a turnover of $12 billion figuring double to the previous year, with around a sale of 61 million sets. Though some of its design may reflect iPhone models, Apple hasnâ€™t taken down any legal implication, but the firm U.S. vice president remarked Xiaomi to its theft and criticized on protection of its intellectual property being weak. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>But Xiaomiâ€™s marketing department spokesperson in an interview with AFP clarified in regard to the allegation and answered back to examine the model more closely to cite out the differences.'),
(58, '<img src="uploads/neeraj/projectnotesPic/2015-01-13_02:01:39pm_drone-camera-970x0.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> The Federal Aviation Administrationâ€™s widespread ban on the commercial use of drones has upset many businesses keen to exploit the technology, among them news outlets that see it as an effective and low-cost option for capturing engaging imagery for TV reports. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>That all looks set to change, however, as CNN announced Monday itâ€™s struck a deal with the FAA to â€œadvance effortsâ€ to integrate unmanned aerial vehicle (UAVs) into the newsgathering process. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>CNN senior vice president David Vigilante said the aim was to â€œget beyond hobby-grade equipment and to establish what options are available and workable to produce high quality video journalism using various types of UAVs and camera setups.â€ <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Read more: http://www.digitaltrends.com/photography/cnn-to-test-drones-for-news-reports-after-nod-from-faa/#ixzz3Oi53MYgz <br/> <s>Follow us: @digitaltrends on Twitter | digitaltrendsftw on Facebook <br/> <s>'),
(59, '<img src="uploads/neeraj/projectnotesPic/2015-01-13_02:05:08pm_Prynt.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> Put bluntly, the Prynt Case is essentially a slim dock that clips onto your phone and prints the pictures you take directly after you snap them. Now, despite what its name would lead you to believe, the case doesnâ€™t require ink to function. Instead it takes a page from the Polaroid playbook and uses special paper to create the image, so youâ€™ll never have to worry about buying cartridges. Early versions of the device took about 50 seconds to print an image, but the more polished version we demoed at CES only needed about 30 to spit out the selfie we snapped at the booth. Prynt plans to launch a Kickstarter campaign later on in January to get the printer off the ground, so stay tuned for more information on features and pricing. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Read more: http://www.digitaltrends.com/cool-tech/awesome-tech-you-cant-buy-yet-ces-2015-edition/#ixzz3Oi5hxnDZ <br/> <s> <br/> <s>'),
(60, '<img src="uploads/neeraj/projectnotesPic/2015-01-13_02:11:44pm_motorola-moto-g-rear-panel-635.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> Customers of devices like the Moto G and Moto E in India are tirelessly waiting for the Android 5.0 Lollipop update to pop up. Although Motorola promised to send out the updates by December, the users are still waiting. Today, a company official has posted a detailed reassurance on Google  telling users that an update is on its way. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Motorola has only sent out the Lollipop update to the 2014 Moto X as of now, so there are multiple devices waiting in line to receive the coveted update. The company is reportedly sending out invites for a <a>quot;soak test<a>quot; of Android 5.0.2, which is a little surprising as Google is yet to roll out this OTA to its Nexus devices. The update was believed to be designed specifically for the Nexus 7 tablet, but it<r>s likely that Motorola wants its users to have the latest version of Android. <br/> <s> <br/> <s><a>quot;Users on the 1st generation Moto products need to make sure they have the latest Motorola Updates Services from the Play Store. If you don<r>t see it showing in your list of apps available for update (or it shows as not compatible) don<r>t worry, it<r>ll be available for you to download it really soon. <br/> <s>Updates of this nature take time. It<r>s no secret that when 5.0 launched it still had bugs. And, when we update our products, we end up finding more bugs that need to be fixed. There are a lot of reasons for what that happen, but, basically, each phone has a unique set of components and a way they interact. When Google creates a new release, they don<r>t validate it for all the possible combinations there are, and they won<r>t fix anything that<r>s not reproducible on a Nexus device, that<r>s our job,<a>quot; said Luciano Carvalho, a software engineer over at Motorola. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>We should expect the 2013 and 2014 Moto G as well as the first gen Moto X to receive the update sometime soon. The budget ranged Moto E might have some waiting to do, however.'),
(61, '<iframe class="youtube" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/PjMVOFrEj9o "frameborder="0" allowfullscreen ></iframe><br/> Music, healthcare and educational products dominated the Las Vegas Convention Center as well as the Venetian/Sands Expo areas of the International CES (Consumer Electronics Show). <br/> <s>Today we start at the Convention Center with Music-Cat Technology <r>Play It<r> EZ Instruments, a Guitar Hero-like product that should be offered in public/private school music departments everywhere. Made in China, Music-Cat makes learning to play piano, drums and string instruments as easy and fun as video games. <br/> <s>Palo Alto Tech<r>s Cool Glass One (also made in China) is wearable 007-type technology that looks like eyeglasses, but with a minor finger adjustment, records images, sound and video. Looks like they <r>borrowed<r> it from Google glass at a much lower price. <br/> <s>From Taiwan, Fantasma Owl On-Wheel-Lighting System projects images and lights as bicycle and/or vehicle tires spin -- keeping riders, bikes and cars illuminated. Great for advertising logos, Burningman, night riding, and other events. <br/> <s>Digital brain fitness products from South Korea -- Brainno, by Soso H<a>amp;C Co., Ltd. -- develops brainwave devices and operational software and contents. BrainnO exercises the mind and should be marketed to healthcare facilities that specialize in ADD, ADHD, Alzheimer<r>s, Dementia, Depression .... The headset sensors detect brain waves and the program suggests favorite colors and music to help relax the mind, while concentration games train and exercise the most complex computer known to man. It<r>s a No BrainNO ;) <br/> <s>CES 2015 at the beautiful Venetian Luxury Resort Hotel Casino. <br/> <s>WEO Technology wireless headsets deliver clear sound, while looking like sci-fi Hi-Tech neckgear; great for daily activities, sports, etc. and available in several colors. Developed and designed in California. <br/> <s>3-D priniting, robots and more. <br/> <s>Yikes! Wish we had more time. <br/> <s>https://www.paloaltonetworks.com/cont... <br/> <s>http://fantasmaowl.com <br/> <s>http://soso-g.co.kr/twfo/en <br/> <s>http://weotech.com'),
(62, '<iframe class="youtube" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/9X38yTxl-fA "frameborder="0" allowfullscreen ></iframe><br/> 2015 Alfa Romeo 4C Spider 1750 CC Turbocharged Dual Intercooler 4-Cylinder Engine 136 HP <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The Alfa Romeo 4C Spider name recalls the brand<r>s great sporting tradition: the acronyms 8C and 6C in the 1930s and 1940s distinguished racing and road cars fitted with powerful eight- and six-cylinder engines. Like the award-winning 4C Coupe, the all-new 2015 Alfa Romeo 4C Spider model<r>s designation is a return to <a>quot;the great Alfa Romeos<a>quot; and continues this tradition with the innovative all-aluminum 1750 cc turbocharged direct injection, dual intercooler four-cylinder engine, delivering an impressive 136 horsepower-per-liter. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>With seating for two, panoramic views and the soundtrack of an Italian performance-tuned engine and exhaust, Spiders are among the most exhilarating experiences in motoring - and represent the very core of Alfa Romeo<r>s DNA and heritage. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The 4C Spider draws from a bloodline that includes some of the most purpose-built performance models that illustrate lightness and efficiency with undeniable Alfa Romeo style: the aluminum-bodied 8C 2900 B Touring (1938); the 1900 C52 <a>quot;Flying Saucer<a>quot; (1952), which could exceed 140 mph (230 kph); and most notably the legendary 33 Stradale (1967) with its mid-engine and magnesium alloy and steel tube chassis <a>quot;clothed<a>quot; by groundbreaking styling, which is functional and distinctly Italian. And now it is the 4C Spider<r>s turn to deliver the driving thrill, performance and unforgettable emotion that only an Alfa Romeo Spider provokes. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Groundbreaking and seductive Italian style <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Continuing the groundbreaking theme of technology, performance and Italian style, the all-new 2015 Alfa Romeo 4C Spider builds upon the brand<r>s journey, which was embarked upon with the 8C Competizione (2008), 8C Spider (2009), 4C Coupe (2015), and most recently, the 4C Spider Concept, which debuted at the 84th International Geneva Motor Show. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Inspired by the 33 Stradale, the all-new Alfa Romeo 4C Spider transcends this legendary racecar<r>s mid-engine body forms and follows its purposeful and lightweight performance tradition with sheet-molded compound (SMC) composite panels forming its seductive Italian design, and <a>quot;clothing<a>quot; its state-of-the-art carbon fiber monocoque chassis and all-aluminum 1750 cc turbocharged, direct-injected engine. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Covering the <a>quot;beating heart<a>quot; of this Italian supercar is a deck-lid with three functional heat extractors and an aerodynamically tuned spoiler. And it<r>s from the 4C Spider<r>s <a>quot;beating heart<a>quot; where every other design element starts: two muscular forms straddle the rear hood and elevate the body above the cockpit<r>s beltline for visual strength and foundation for the black or available carbon fiber <a>quot;halo.<a>quot; The rear fascia and round rear LED illuminated taillamps blend into the muscular rear wings for a powerful stance, while stylistically incorporating large functional air intakes to cool the engine. Below, dual exhausts are mounted at the corners and highlight the 4C Spider<r>s supercar stance. Inspired by the 4C Spider Concept, an all-new, Akrapovic dual-mode center-mounted performance exhaust system will be available on the 4C Spider (late availability). <br/> <s> <br/> <s>On each side of the all-new 4C Spider, the sculpted air intakes spring a muscular and dynamic form that lead elegantly into the headlamps. Highlighting its exotic monocoque is a carbon fiber windshield frame, which promotes strength and lightness, while providing the attachment points for the removable, stowable cloth roof, or available exposed carbon fiber hardtop (late availability). <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Leading from the 4C Spider<r>s windshield and down the hood are two muscular hood forms, which naturally conclude at the signature Alfa Romeo shield-shaped grille and emblem. Together with the two side air intakes designed in the front fascia, the 4C Spider forms the famous <a>quot;Trilobo,<a>quot; a significant facet of Alfa Romeo<r>s distinctive design. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Performance-focused cockpit <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The all-new 2015 Alfa Romeo 4C Spider<r>s cockpit is inspired from racing, purpose built with only the essential driving components stylistically integrated. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The Alfa Romeo 4C Spider features two composite-framed sport seats with standard leather and an exposed carbon fiber monocoque that exemplifies its race-inspired technologies. Furthermore, a driver-oriented cockpit with flat-bottom, leather performance steering wheel with paddle-shifters and aluminum pedals speak to the brand<r>s racing spirit. For an upscale look, the fully wrapped premium-leather interior with accent stitching is standard on the Alfa Romeo 4C Spider, as are unique carbon fiber vent surrounds. Highlighting the use of advanced technology is a 7-inch full-color driver information display (DID) cluster, which displays vehicle information through high-impact graphics to keep the driver focused on the road, or track, ahead.'),
(63, '<img src="uploads/rajnish/articlePic/2015-01-13_11:38:12pm_mars orbitor.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/>  <br/> <s>Indiaâ€™s Mars Orbiter programme team has won the 2015 Space Pioneer Award in the science and engineering category from the US based National Space Society (NSS), the society said. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>In a statement issued in Washington on Monday, the NSS said its 2015 Space Pioneer Award in the science and engineering category has been won by the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) Mars Orbiter Programme team. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>â€œThis award will be presented to an ISRO representative during the National Space Societyâ€™s 2015 International Space Development Conference, the 34th ISDC, to be held in Toronto, Canada,â€ the statement said. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The conference will run form May 20-24. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>According to the NSS, Indiaâ€™s Mars Orbiter launched on Nov 5, 2013 that went into Mars orbit on Sep 24, 2014 achieved two significant mission firsts in terms of an Indian spacecraft that has gone into orbit around Mars on the very first try and that no other country has ever done this. Secondly, the spacecraft is in an elliptical orbit with a high apoapsis, and has a high resolution camera which is taking full-disk color imagery of Mars. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Very few full disk images have ever been taken in the past, mostly on approach to the planet, as most imaging is done looking straight down in mapping mode. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>These images will aid planetary scientists. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The Mars Orbiter programme team located in Bangalore is headed by Mylswamy Annadurai, the statement said. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The NSS is an independent non-profit educational membership organization dedicated to the creation of a space faring civilization. <br/> <s>h/t: http://goo.gl/qmRYOs'),
(64, '<img src="uploads/shruti/articlePic/2015-01-14_09:20:44am_18-Mistakes-That-Kill-Startups.png.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> <s> <br/> <s>Â If you have a list of all the things you shouldnâ€™t do, you can turn that into a recipe for succeeding just by negating list of mistakes. Have a look on startup mistakes, you should avoid. <s><br/> <s>Â Below you will find the 18 startup mistakes: <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â #1. Single Founder: As a single founder you have almost zero chance of getting funding from Paul Graham. Why? Itâ€™s not a coincidence, he says, that founders who succeeded did so as a team of at least two. <s><br/> <s>Â #2. Bad Location â€“ you can change everything about a house but its location. Likewise, if your startup is in a bad location, you canâ€™t change the nature of that location. Itâ€™s easier to move the startup. Where to? Silicon Valley. <s><br/> <s>Â #3. Marginal Niche â€“ by choosing an obscure niche a startup may paint themselves in a corner. If you are afraid of competition, this is not the way to avoid it. <s><br/> <s>Â #4. Derivative Idea â€“ there are only so many Twitters for pet owners one can come up with. The bottom line is that the Google of tomorrow will not be like Google. <s><br/> <s>Â #5. Obstinacy â€“ or inability to adapt kills startups who would have survived had they not been too stubborn to see what their users were telling them. <s><br/> <s>Â #6. Hiring Bad Programmers â€“ knowing a good programmer from a bad one often takes being a good one yourself, or having a trusted one on your team. Exceptional programmers are always in short supply. So the odds are stacked up against hiring good ones. <s><br/> <s>Â #7. Choosing the Wrong Platform â€“ how fast you can scale will determine whether your startup lives or dies once you get traction. On the wrong platform scalability will be the bottleneck. And users often donâ€™t wait for you to figure it out. <s><br/> <s>Â  #8. Slowness in Launching â€“ before you actually launch you are in the dark about whether your startup should even exist. The longer you delay the launch the more you delay getting the answer. If you are afraid to know what the answer is, you might want to ask yourself why. <s><br/> <s>Â #9. Launching Too Early â€“ launch too early, though, and you may be completely unprepared to handle your growth, or worse yet to present a usable product. <s><br/> <s>Â #10. Having No Specific User in Mind â€“ somewhere someone will for sure be interested in your product, you just donâ€™t know who yet? Sounds like those people may not exist. Be sure to check. <s><br/> <s>Â #11. Raising Too Little Money â€“ you get what you spend on. With too little money you may not be able to flesh out your product in to its full potential. <s><br/> <s>Â #12. Spending Too Much â€“ spending too much before you grew enough to have the numbers to raise the next round, and you are out of cash, which often spells the end. <s><br/> <s>Â #13. Raising Too Much Money â€“ raising too much will likely make you feel like a huge success even before you made anything useful. At the end of the day itâ€™s users, not investors, you want to impress the most. <s><br/> <s>Â #14. Poor Investor Management â€“ if the choice is between making investors happy or making your users happy, always choose the users. If the user is happy your investors will make money eventually. <s><br/> <s>Â #15. Sacrificing Users to (Supposed) Profit â€“ you can always make money later. This however, cannot be said about making users happy. You need to make something they want now. <s><br/> <s>Â #16. Not Wanting to Get Your Hands Dirty â€“ you canâ€™t solve all your problems with coding. Businesses are built on relationships. Go out and meet those people. <s><br/> <s>Â #17. Fights Between Founders â€“ founder conflict is too common. Founders being ambitious people are almost bound to disagree. <s><br/> <s>Â #18. A Half-Hearted Effort â€“ a lack of determination to see the startup through to the end is not rare. If you feel like you have other options in life than building your startup, you will probably mentally hang on to them. <s><br/> <s>Â For more information check out at : http://goo.gl/PxoOx1 <s><br/> <s>Â Ref: http://goo.gl/5h5zsh'),
(65, '<img src="uploads/rajnish/articlePic/2015-01-14_12:30:53pm_isro view.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/>  <br/> <s>The fourth navigation satellite of the country is getting ready for launch in March, and it will be another step forward for India in evolving its own navigation satellite system and not depend on the Geographical Positioning System (GPS) service of the U.S. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Cryogenic propulsion systems on board PSLV-C27 rocket that will launch the satellite are being developed by scientists of the ISRO Propulsion Complex at Mahendragiri in Tirunelveli district. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>S. Ingersol, group director of the complex, told The Hindu, â€œTotally, seven satellites are required to be launched to complete the configuration under the Indian Regional Navigation Satellite System (IRNSS) and already three had been launched. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Dr. Ingersol said launch of the remaining four satellites would be completed in one year and after that Indiaâ€™s dependency on the U.S. for GPS service would be significantly reduced. â€œThis will trigger the much-needed development in geographic information systems.â€ <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The Mahendragiri complex was developing the second and fourth liquid stages needed for the launch vehicle. <br/> <s> <br/> <s><a>quot;Advance research by ISRO scientists has made India go for launching heavier satellites of three to four tonnes from our own soil,<a>quot; he said. <s><br/> <s>Reference: http://goo.gl/jCj1r7'),
(66, '<img src="uploads/rajnish/projectnotesPic/2015-01-14_12:42:03pm_moonbase_free3d printing.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/>  <br/> <s>Imagine that the printer hooked up to your home computer could make anything. Lost your toothbrush? No problem. Print it. Need new shoes, a new dress, new cleats? Just instruct your computer to tell that machine what style and size you want. Then print, print and print some more. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Already, some companies are figuring out how to print cells as the first step in creating a new organ for transplanting into people. One company has just printed most of a working electric car. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>In a few years, 3-D printing could drastically change the world of manufacturing. Already, creative people -they call themselves makers - have formed communities to share computer files that give the directions for making their novel creations <br/> <s> <br/> <s>According to legend, the French sculptor Auguste Rodin once explained: â€œI choose a block of marble and chop off whatever I donâ€™t need.â€ This means he used subtraction to sculpt his creations. 3-D printing does the opposite: It adds layers, one at a time, to build something from the bottom up. Thatâ€™s why some engineers refer to 3-D printing as additive manufacturing. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>For 3-D printing, someone must create a computer file that describes a desired object in three dimensions. This blueprint includes the size, shape and color of the thing to be printed. Then someone tells the computer to digitally â€œsliceâ€ that object into virtual slivers. The printer then builds each slice, one thin layer at a time. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Some printers spit out metal. Others spray a liquid that will harden into plastic. Some manufacturers are using special printers to spray out chocolate, cheese or other foods to make custom products. In 2013, one biomedical research company used plastic to 3-D print 75 percent of a manâ€™s skull, which was then surgically implanted into the patient. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The European Space Agency has begun research to see if it can â€œprintâ€ a moon base using lunar soil. NASA, the American space agency, is investigating the idea of using 3-D printing to create food for astronauts on deep-space missions. <br/> <s>Reference: http://goo.gl/gFyu97 <br/> <s>Author Information: http://goo.gl/ce8Ryg'),
(67, '<img src="uploads/rajnish/challengePic/2015-01-14_04:18:55pm_alian horizon.png.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /> <br/>  <br/> <s>It may look like some kind of alien landscape, but this photo shows a super-rare combination of solar phenomena happening right here on Earth. <br/> <s>The image was captured by Joshua Thomas who emailed the US National Weather Service (NWS) in Texas to find out what was going on. <br/> <s>With a little help from researchers at Atmospheric Optics, the NWS annotated the image, describing each of the optical phenomena that are happening at once, and posted it to Facebook. While on their own most aren<r>t that rare, the combination is pretty mind-blowing. <br/> <s>But what caused the display? The majority of these phenomena, such as 22Âº halos, Sun pillars and Sun dogs, are caused by sunlight interacting with ice crystals in the atmosphere. So it seems that the cold weather, combined with the angle of the Sun at sunrise, led to the unlikely appearance of so many arcs and halos at once. <br/> <s>The whole thing is just so pretty. It<r>s almost enough to make this Sun lover want to head north to colder climates. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Reference: http://goo.gl/Jy6dhq <br/> <s>'),
