(70, '<img src="uploads/rajnish/articlePic/2015-01-14_09:18:32pm_AIGettyImagesRF.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> <s> <br/> <s>Â Technology is constantly evolving. We have witnessed numerous innovations in the world of technology in this year. However, the evolution process of technology is slow. The incremental changes in technology are occasional. Letâ€™s take a look at 5 tech trends for 2015. <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â 1. Big Data: Big Data development is tremendous and unstoppable. We are generating tremendous amount of data. Eric Schmidt, Chairman of Google had said, we generate five exabytes of data every two days. He had made the statement in 2010. The number must have doubled by now. We are capturing data through mobile apps, sensors, websites and this rate is expected regularly in 2015 too. <s><br/> <s>Â Companies like IBM, Intel are expected to come up with powerful decision making tools to analyse this piles of data in 2015. IBM is working on a super computer project that can introduce cognitive computing to all industries. IBM is also working another project using Twitterâ€™s data. Intel is building hardware platform for enterprises to bring Big Data processing. The rate of development in this data is expected to increase exponentially in 2015. <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â 2. Artificial Intelligence: Artificial Intelligence can true bring the data revolution. Microsoft is using machine learning to analyse speech and conversations. Skypeâ€™s new Translator app can perform real-time, bidirectional translations. The company is working on a feature that can even mimic the accept of other languages. <s><br/> <s>Â Eugene Groostman beat proved the quality in Turing test this year. This research can lead to building human like thought system processor in future. Demis Hassabis from Google is trying to solve intelligence using his startup, DeepMind. It is a recreating human neurons in silicon and code. Artificial intelligence certainly has a great potential to grow and nurture in 2015. <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â 3. Robots: We will get to see futuristic version of robots in 2015. These futuristic robots can be used in manufacturing industry. Interactive Robotics Group team at MIT is working pretty hard on manufacturing robots that can work on assembly line. Most of these robots will work in highly controlled environment, away from human beings. <s><br/> <s>Â Amazon is working on Rabo-Stow robotic arms that can pick things from shelves. And the mobile can control the things in the factory. Personal robots like Jibo and Pepper are great example of what the future with robots in day-to-day life is going to look like. MIT professor, Sangbae Kimâ€™s Cheeta robot can run really fast. He looks at his model has futuristic driverless car. <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â 4. Batteries: Most consumer manufacturing companies are working on future battery technology. Intel, Qualcomm, Nvidia, AMD and Texas instruments are building on more efficient mobile CPUs that can consume minimal battery power. The chemical science will have a major breakthrough in coming year. <s><br/> <s>Â Scientists are working on sodium-based, complex hydride. It can lead to cheaper and more efficient battery power. Applied Material research will lead to advance solid state battery technology which can hold much more power than traditional lithium ion battery. New battery technology will have distinct possibilities. Wireless charging was introduced in 2013 but, we will see major advances in wireless charging in 2015. We just need more wireless charging gadgets, charging stations. All such gadgets will probably flood the markets in coming year. <s><br/> <s>Â  <s><br/> <s>Â 5. Flexible Displays: We can finally expect to see the flexible displays in 2015. Curved display products like LGâ€™s curved HDTV, Samsung Gear Git have been launched in this year. However electronic gadgets with proper flexible displays have been a dream product. We can expect to see thin and flexible displays in coming year. <s><br/> <s>Â Intel is reportedly working on a product with drinking components and removable wires through WiDi (Wireless Display) technology. The potential of flexible display products is tremendous. This can be a great innovation for biometric password tools, smart home and internet of things. Flexible displays can also be used in wearable gadgets. <s><br/> <s>Â Content from efytimes <s><br/> <s>Â More from author: http://azure.efytimes.com/?author=2'),
(71, '<img src="uploads/rajnish/challengePic/2015-01-14_09:29:30pm_open source.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/>  <br/> <s>We have been using open source software for quite a long time now. Many tech companies are seen adopting to open source technologies lately. Even government agencies are replacing proprietary software with open source. Most of the open source projects are backed by strong active community of developers. <br/> <s>Some open source projects have really high potential. As a developer, it is important that you give back something to the open source community. Here is a list of five high-potential startups that you should look forward to join in 2015. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>1. BRL-CAD: <br/> <s>BRL-CAD is a powerful and dynamic 3D modeling system. This can be very helpful for coders, testers and even trainers and professional UI designers. The code is available online but, it is quite complex. If you are a programmer, you can help in cleaning up the code. There are numerous tasks that you can do to help BRL-CAD project. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>2. Speed Dreams: <br/> <s>Speed Dreams is a 3D motorsport simulation and racing game. The project supports Windows and Linux, the Mac OS version is still under development. The lead developers team is looking for developers, designers and people to write documentation. If you are a gamer, you can join Speed Dreams as the community shares same passion for gaming and open source. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>3. OpenMRS: <br/> <s>OpenMRS is a software project that actually helps people. The platform mainly focuses on healthcare sector. The project is looking for programmers, testers, IT support, technical writers, UI designers and translators. You can join the OpenMRS community and discuss ideas, suggest new features, fix bugs or even promote the project on social media. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>4. Audacity: <br/> <s>Audacity is a popular sound recording and editing software. The software has been around since May 2000 and is constantly improving. Audacity is looking for range of contributors. Developers, testers, script writers, anyone can help the project to grow and develop. If you are good with language, you can help in writing the documentation of the project too. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>5. FLOSS Manuals: <br/> <s>FLOSS Manuals, as the name suggests, is the library of software and open source manuals. The project doesn<r>t need designers or testers. It needs writers. If you think you are good with words, you can definitely help in the development of FLOSS Manuals. Best thing about FLOSS Manuals is you don<r>t have to jump right in and start from scratch. You can take help of books and update the existing available documentation or fix typos and errors. <s><br/> <s>Content from efytimes, http://www.efytimes.com'),
(72, 'Http status codes have nXX family with n upto 5. The Internet Assigned Numbers Authority (IANA) maintains the official registry of HTTP status codes. The first digit of the status code specifies one of five classes of response. Here list of 4xx family which occurs frequently on client<r>s side. <s><br/> <s>Brief view about nXX family. <br/> <s>1xx: <s><br/> <s>1xx Informational (100, 101, 102, 103, 122) <br/> <s>2xx: Success (200 to 208 and 226) <br/> <s>3xx: redirection (300 to 308) <br/> <s>4xx: client errors <br/> <s>5xx: server error (500 to 509, 598, 599) <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 400: Bad Request- Server can<r>t understand commands due to a syntax error <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 401: Unauthorized- Similar to 403, but specifically for when the required information has not been given <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 402: Payment Required- This basically means a payment or any other further action is required to access the page <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 403: Forbidden- this means that the site is password protected and/or you don<r>t have permission to access it <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 404: Not Found- This is MOST LIKEY the most common error. This occurs when a site cannot be found <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 405: Method Not Allowed- A request Method is not supported with the resource. Like read only stuff <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 406: Not Acceptable- This means that something was not deemed acceptable according to the Accept headers sent in the request. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 407: Proxy Authentication Required- The client first has to authenticate its proxy <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 408: Request Timeout- This means that the server timed out while waiting to perform a task. It usually happens when you try to connect to a website and it takes too long <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 409: Conflict- Indicates that the request could not be processed because of conflict in the request, such as an edit conflict in the case of multiple updates. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 410: Gone- Indicates that the resource requested is no longer available and will not be available again. This should be used when a resource has been intentionally removed and the resource should be purged. Upon receiving a 410 status code, the client should not request the resource again in the future. Clients such as search engines should remove the resource from their indices. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 411: Length Required- The request did not specify the length of its content, which is required by the requested resource. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 412: Precondition Failed- The server does not meet one of the preconditions that the requester put on the request. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 413: Request Entity Too Large- The request is larger than the server is willing or able to process. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 414: Request-URI Too Long- The URI provided was too long for the server to process. Often the result of too much data being encoded as a query-string of a GET request, in which case it should be converted to a POST request. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 415: Unsupported Media Type- The request entity has a media type which the server or resource does not support. For example, the client uploads an image as image/svg xml, but the server requires that images use a different format. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 416: Requested Range Not Satisfiable- The client has asked for a portion of the file (byte serving), but the server cannot supply that portion. For example, if the client asked for a part of the file that lies beyond the end of the file. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 417: Expectation Failed- The server cannot meet the requirements of the Expect request-header field. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 418: I<r>m a teapot- This code was defined in 1998 as one of the traditional IETF April Fools<r> jokes, in RFC 2324, Hyper Text Coffee Pot Control Protocol, and is not expected to be implemented by actual HTTP servers. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 419: Authentication Timeout- Not a part of the HTTP standard, 419 Authentication Timeout denotes that previously valid authentication has expired. It is used as an alternative to 401 Unauthorized in order to differentiate from otherwise authenticated clients being denied access to specific server resources. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 420: Method Failure- Not part of the HTTP standard, but defined by Spring in the HttpStatus class to be used when a method failed. This status code is deprecated by Spring. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 420: Enhance Your Calm (Twitter): Not part of the HTTP standard, but returned by version 1 of the Twitter Search and Trends API when the client is being rate limited.[15] Other services may wish to implement the 429 Too Many Requests response code instead. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 422: Unprocessable Entity- The request was well-formed but was unable to be followed due to semantic errors. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 423: Locked- The resource that is being accessed is locked. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 424: Failed Dependency- The request failed due to failure of a previous request. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 426: Upgrade Required- The client should switch to a different protocol such as TLS/1.0. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 428: Precondition Required- The origin server requires the request to be conditional. Intended to prevent <a>quot;the <r>lost update<r> problem, where a client GETs a resource<r>s state, modifies it, and PUTs it back to the server, when meanwhile a third party has modified the state on the server, leading to a conflict.<a>quot; <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 429: Too Many Requests- The user has sent too many requests in a given amount of time. Intended for use with rate limiting schemes. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 431: Request Header Fields Too Large The server is unwilling to process the request because either an individual header field, or all the header fields collectively, are too large. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 440: Login Timeout (Microsoft): A Microsoft extension. Indicates that your session has expired. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 444: No Response (Nginx)- Used in Nginx logs to indicate that the server has returned no information to the client and closed the connection.. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 449: Retry With (Microsoft)- A Microsoft extension. The request should be retried after performing the appropriate action. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 450: Blocked by Windows Parental Controls (Microsoft)- A Microsoft extension. This error is given when Windows Parental Controls are turned on and are blocking access to the given webpage. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 451: Unavailable For Legal Reasons (Internet draft)- Defined in the internet draft <a>quot;A New HTTP Status Code for Legally-restricted Resources<a>quot;. Intended to be used when resource access is denied for legal reasons, e.g. censorship or government-mandated blocked access. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 451: Redirect (Microsoft)- Used in Exchange ActiveSync if there either is a more efficient server to use or the server cannot access the users<r> mailbox. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 494: Request Header Too Large (Nginx)- Nginx internal code similar to 431 but it was introduced earlier in version 0.9.4. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 495: Cert Error (Nginx)- Nginx internal code used when SSL client certificate error occurred to distinguish it from 4XX in a log and an error page redirection. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 496: No Cert (Nginx)- Nginx internal code used when client didn<r>t provide certificate to distinguish it from 4XX in a log and an error page redirection. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 497: HTTP to HTTPS (Nginx)- Nginx internal code used for the plain HTTP requests that are sent to HTTPS port to distinguish it from 4XX in a log and an error page redirection. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 498: Token expired/invalid (Esri)- Returned by ArcGIS for Server. A code of 498 indicates an expired or otherwise invalid token. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 499: Client Closed Request (Nginx)- Used in Nginx logs to indicate when the connection has been closed by client while the server is still processing its request, making server unable to send a status code back. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Error 499: Token required (Esri)- Returned by ArcGIS for Server. A code of 499 indicates that a token is required.'),
