(149, '<img src="uploads/rahul/projectnotesPic/2015-01-26_01:04:45pm_20130402115725_coffee-workspace.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> Now a days cloud are becoming very popular organization are moving toward cloud service architecture. Depending on the requirement organizations move toward specific architecture SaaS, PaaS or IaaS cite Depending on the size of the organization move toward Public, Private or Hybrid cloud service architecture. Here in this paper we will explore the service porting to cloud. Which will use SaaS service of the cloud. Which can be deployed at any of cloud service architecture. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Smart Software Separator can be useful for the Cloud service providing organizations and as well as for the Cloud service developers. The organization which also wants to deploy there single machine service to the cloud can also take benefit of the tool. Which will decrease the deployment cost and give a effective result. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Automatic porting of service from client side user interface to web base user interface, by using the Web sockets the client side user interface can communicate to the server side program. Which will reside at the cloud. <s><br/> <s> <br/> <s>Here the porting program will also separate the single machine program into client and server program. The separation of client and server program will take place in such a way that the operation requiring less computation can be posted at the client side and they have computation thing can to handle by the server program. By doing such a smart separation we can decrease the network traffic and there will be decrease in operational latency. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Example such as inside Google docs the operation like bolt the text other textual optional functionality can be done at the client side only. Such as in a hypostatical example, suppose we are running C IDE as SaaS inside the cloud, in case of a development process there are two basic things which are needed to be solved first computational less part such as the text edition functionality to the user such as copy, cut, paste, bold, taken input from the user and other is the computation executive part that take most of the computation of the process. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>By using the above smart procedure of software porting the system will lead to the basic two benefits the decrease in the latency and the decrease in the network traffic. That will finally lead to benefit to increase in the user interaction level with the system. In the following paper we will literature survey followed by we will see various method to solve the problem and then we will go through the Smart Software Separation procedure. Followed we will go to detail architecture and algorithm. Then to the implementation plan.'),
(150, '<img src="uploads/rahul/projectnotesPic/2015-01-26_01:13:05pm_generalmethod.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> In the general method we need to have some single machine software which we want to port as a web service. In this general method we can deploy that single machine software inside the cloud as SaaS. To access such software we need to have some remote service software deployed at the service side which <br/> <s>will deliver the software instance to some client Remote Access Software. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>There are various remote access software currently present such as Remote desktop which work on the bases of RDP(remote desktop protocol), VNC(Virtual network connect) which work on the image cooperation technique. <s><br/> <s> <br/> <s>Single machine software: This is the software which we want to convert into a web service and deploy on the cloud as SaaS. This software is designed to deploy on a single machine. We dont have any direct machines to convert it as a web services. <s><br/> <s> <br/> <s>Putting on the Cloud: In this method we deploy the software on the cloud and forward the video port of the software to the remote access software.[video port forwarding text]. That server software used to transmit the instance to the client. Client software delivers the interface to the user. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Client access through Remote Access Software: The GUI user interface forwarded by the server program is delivered to the user at client side by using this client side software. This client side software forward the user input(mouse and keyboard) to the server program and server forwards it to the user software on server and in reverse user software send the response to the client software.'),
(151, '<img src="uploads/rahul/projectnotesPic/2015-01-26_01:17:59pm_optimizedmethod.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> As shown in the figure the single machine software codes are given to the designing team in order to separate the code into server side program and the client side program. The team analyse the code and separate them <br/> <s>accordingly and connect them with the help of the sockets. Here the it depended on the designing team to divide the software as client as a interface and server as a processing end or put the less computation thing on the client side and huge computation operation at the server side. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Manual Code Separation and Socketifing: <br/> <s> <br/> <s> Here the designing and coding team analyse and separate the code according the requirement. Code separation can be done in two ways just separating the user interface and the computational part and porting the user interface at the client side and the computation part at the server side or the second method can be dividing the codes into two part high computational part and the low computational part. Putting the high computational part at the sever side and low computational part at the client side. The decision will be in heads of the designing team. They can go for any approach the want. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Server Side Program: <s><br/> <s>There is the high computational handling part, which will also responsible for the handling of storage and other issue like access time and computation power. This server side program will be deployed at the cloud as SaaS. Users can user this service by using a webbrowser. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Client side program: This program will be used to provide user interface to the user of the web service. This program may or may not preform some computational task which will be completely dependent on the designers or the service.'),
(152, '<img src="uploads/rahul/projectnotesPic/2015-01-26_01:34:59pm_Detailarch.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> Overview: <br/> <s>Smart Software Separation: this is very similar to Optimized method but here all work which is done by the designer and the coders is automated. They Single machine software will go for Class method profiling and based on threshold separating the high computational code and low computational codes. Accordingly putting the codes at severs and client end. The communication in between the server and client can take place through the sockets. Client codes should be converted into the JavaScript and HTML by using the services like Java2javascript or Goggle web tool kit. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Detail Architecture of Smart Software Separater: <br/> <s>Here we can see that how that working of Smart Software Saparater will going to work. Various component involve inside the Smart Software coverter. Some of the components are currently existing and some of them are needed to be developed such are component like code converter are currently existen component like Java2Javascript[cite] is currently existen . Java2Javascript is a product of Oracle . Java2Javascript takes java code and convert it into javascript codes. Similar product of Google also exist that is known as Google <br/> <s>web tool kit. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>But the decision of which code to be putted at client side and server side should be taken based on the running time complexity of the code. Which can only be profiled by running the Single machine software in the real time envirnment. The method which are have more complexity then threshold should be kept at the sever side and may exicute in some sever side programing language or they can also exicute in there native programming language. Communication between the server and client can take place by the sockets . Socketise should be developed that can put the socket in order to communicate are relative place. There is no tool currently existen which can socketify the given code according to the user requirnment. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Source Code(Java): <s><br/> <s>Here in the initial phase we are take only the java language as our source language. It is he language of the Single Machine Software. Language of the program which is needed to be converted. These <br/> <s>source codes will go to user interface separater in order to separate the user interface from the source code. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>User Interface Separater: <s><br/> <s>Interface part should have to be at the client side in respect itâ€™s complexityis less or more then the threshold. Generaly it found that the user interface requires less processing[cite to....]. So , separating these code before the further separation will be a precation for the system. So that the interface code should always at the client side Here the interface code can be in the Swing(java) or in java serverlet . These are basic interface which are provided for some jave utility. Whereever the user interface separater find that the methods are interacting with none interfacing object. It will put a mark there. The marking done by the Interface separater will be read by the socketiser in order to put there socket and let the interface and other codes communicate over the network. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Software Class Profiling: Here in this method the software will profile various method of the class and find the running time complexty of 2nd or 3rd level of class in class model. The 2nd or 3rd level are those classes which are classed by 1st or 2nd level of object in the running time calling Herirarche of the code at the running time. <s><br/> <s> <br/> <s> <s>After profile the method those data will be store in a table with method and class detail which crosponig running time complixity. This data will be used by the code separater in order to find the serve side code and the client side codes. The codes which will have less complaxity then the threshold will be putted at the client side other will be putted at the server side. Decision of code separation will take on the bases of the thrashold . Thrashold is a per-defined heristic number which can be calculated of gussed on the bases on client ability to process. Code which are less then thrashold will be input inside java2javascript or google webket tool which will give us the out put in HTML5 and Javascript. Which can run at client side by using some web browser. <br/> <s>But the process of porting is yet not over , after the sparation and covertion there is need of a importent step introducing socket inside the codes. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Socketiser: <br/> <s> This component will be used to introduce socket inside the client and the server code which is separated based on the thrashold. based on the table information and the mark on the interface code it will introduce <br/> <s>the sockets in between the codes. Here some importent points will also be concidered. The introduction of socket will only take place at the lower level only i.e on the running time heirarche of code the point will less then threshold and the interface marks which ever at the lower level will be awarded socket introduction <br/> <s>Result: Finally the code will be inside to part one will be in form of HTML and Javascript and other part will be in the form of native language here inside java. Client machine user can access the software now the web software by using the browser on the machine.'),
(153, '<img src="uploads/anil/projectnotesPic/2015-01-26_05:38:09pm_muscular-system.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> The muscular system is the biological system of humans that produces movement. The muscular system, in vertebrates, is controlled through the nervous system, although some muscles, like cardiac muscle, can be completely autonomous. Muscle is contractile tissue and is derived from the mesodermal layer of embryonic germ cells. Without the skeletal muscular system, the bones would be unable to move. Our bodies are equipped with some 600 skeletal muscles to not only put 206 bones into motion, but also to generate as much as 85% of our body heat, maintain our posture, control the openings involved with the entrance and exit of materials, and to express our emotions and thoughts through movements of our facial muscles. Three important structural terms of skeletal muscular system are a muscleâ€™s origin, insertion, and belly. Most muscles are attached to different bones at each end. This assures that each muscle or its tendon will span at least one joint. When a muscle contracts, it causes movement where one bone remains relatively stationary and the other bone will move. The end of the muscle attached to the relatively stationary bone is called the origin, while the end of the muscle attached to the moving bone is called the insertion. Many muscles are narrow at each end, their origin and insertion, and thick in the middle. This thicker middle region is called the belly. <s> Much of muscle contraction occurs without conscious thought and is necessary for survival, like the contraction of the heart or peristalsis, which pushes food through the digestive system. Voluntary muscle contraction is used to move the body and can be finely controlled, such as movements of the finger or gross movements that of the biceps and triceps.'),
(154, '<img src="uploads/anil/projectnotesPic/2015-01-26_06:27:36pm_image008.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/>  The muscular system has three types of muscles. They are: <br/> <s> â€¢ Cardiac muscle <br/> <s> â€¢ Smooth muscle <br/> <s> â€¢ Skeletal muscle <br/> <s> <br/> Cardiac Muscle <br/> <s>The walls of the heart are made of cardiac muscles . When these muscles contract and relax, they circulate blood throughout the body. Cardiac muscles are involuntary. This means they are not controlled consciously like skeletal muscles. Continuous contraction and relaxation of cardiac muscle is necessary for survival. Cardiac muscle does not get tired. It makes the energy it needs to keep the heart beating from birth until death. Another name for cardiac muscle is myocardium. The cardiac cells is the most physically energetic cell in the body, contracting constantly, without tiring, 3 billion times or more in an average human lifespan. By coordinating its beating activity with that of its 3 billion neighbours in the main pump of the human heart, over 7,000 litres of blood are pumped per day, without conscious effort, along 100,000 miles of blood vessels. Coordinated contraction of cardiac muscle cells in the heart propel blood out of the atria and ventricles to the blood vessels of the left/body/systemic and right/lungs/pulmonary circulatory systems. This phenomona is understood as systole of the heart. Cardiac muscle cells, like all tissues in the body, rely on an ample blood supply to deliver oxygen and nutrients and to remove waste products such as carbon dioxide. The coronary arteries fulfill this function. Cardiac muscle is adapted to be highly resistant to fatigue : it has a large number of mitochondria, enabling continuous aerobic respiration via oxidative phosphorylation, numerous myoglobins ( oxygen-storing pigment ) and a good blood supply, which provides nutrients and oxygen. The heart is so tuned to aerobic metabolism that it is unable to pump sufficiently in ischaemic conditions. At basal metabolic rates, about 1% of energy is derived from anaerobic metabolism. This can increase to 10% under moderately hypoxic conditions, but, under more severe hypoxic conditions, not enough energy can be liberated by lactate production to sustain ventricular contractions. In cardiac muscle the cells are in electrical contact through communicating gap junctions. These are important for the orderly spread of excitation through the heart. This starts with the spontaneous depolarisation of the specialised pacemaker cells in the sino-atrial node, spreads via the atria to the atrio-ventricular node and then to the conducting fibres in the Bundle of His (in the intraventricular septum) and the Purkinje system. These cells finally activate the bulk of the ventricular muscle in the chamber walls, in each case through direct electrical contacts. The major causes of cardiovascular disease are tobacco use, physical inactivity, and an unhealthy diet. Tobacco use, an unhealthy diet, and physical inactivity increase the risk of heart attacks and strokes. High blood pressure has no symptoms, but can cause a sudden stroke or heart attack. Diabetes increases the risk of heart attacks and stroke. Being overweight increases the risk of heart attacks and strokes. Low socioeconomic status increases the chances of exposure to risk factors and increases the vulnerability to develop CVD. '),
