(244, 'PHP uses include, include_once, require, require_once for including external files. <s><br/> <s> Â  <s><br/> <s> Â include: include includes a file and throws a warning if the file was not found. Files are included based on the file path given or, if none is given, the include_path specified. If the file isn<r>t found in the include_path, include will finally check in the calling script<r>s own directory and the current working directory before failing. <s><br/> <s> Â require: require includes a file and throws a fatal error(E_COMPILE_ERROR level error) if the file was not found. It will halt the script whereas include only emits a warning (E_WARNING) which allows the script to continue. <s><br/> <s> Â  <s><br/> <s> Â  <s><br/> <s> Â <a>lt;?php Â  <br/> <s> Â  <s><br/> <s> Â  Â  Â 1. require <r>check_include.php<r>; <s><br/> <s> Â  Â  Â 2. //some php statements <s><br/> <s> Â  Â  Â 3. require <r>check_include.php<r>; <s><br/> <s> Â  Â  Â 4. //some php statements <s><br/> <s> Â  Â  Â 5. require <r>check_include.php<r>; <s><br/> <s> Â  Â  Â 6. //some php statements <s><br/> <s> Â  Â  Â 7. require <r>check_include.php<r>; <s><br/> <s> Â  <s><br/> <s> Â ?<a>gt; <s><br/> <s> Â  <s><br/> <s> Â When include/require used, php interpreter interprets from line 1 require is there, if file is found then interpreter interprets whole included file, again on line 3, 5, it will repeat same process. <s><br/> <s> Â  <s><br/> <s> Â include_once: The include_once() statement includes and evaluates the specified file during the execution of the script. This is a behavior similar to the include() statement, with the only difference being that if the code from a file has already been included, it will not be included again. As the name suggests, it will be included just once. <s><br/> <s> Â include_once may be used in cases where the same file might be included and evaluated more than once during a particular execution of a script, so in this case it may help avoid problems such as function redefinitions, variable value reassignments, etc. <s><br/> <s> Â  <s><br/> <s> Â require_once: The require_once() statement includes and evaluates the specified file during the execution of the script. This is a behavior similar to the require() statement, with the only difference being that if the code from a file has already been included, it will not be included again. <s><br/> <s> Â  <s><br/> <s> Â <a>lt;?php <s><br/> <s> Â 1. include_once <r>check_include.php<r>; <s><br/> <s> Â 2. //some php statements <s><br/> <s> Â 3. include_once <r>check_include.php<r>; <s><br/> <s> Â 4. //some php statements <s><br/> <s> Â 5. include_once <r>check_include.php<r>; <s><br/> <s> Â 6. //some php statements <s><br/> <s> Â 7. include_once <r>check_include.php<r>; <s><br/> <s> Â ?<a>gt; <s><br/> <s> Â In case of include_once/require_once: When include/require used, php interpreter interprets from line 1 include_once is there, if file is found then interpreter interprets whole included file and maintains a record for included file in file_handler. So on line 3,5,7 interpreter checks in file_handler if file is included already it will neglect again including line 3,5,7.');
