(256, '<iframe class="youtube" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/xBDrevuomfo "frameborder="0" allowfullscreen ></iframe><br/> You Can Try On Clothes Virtually With MemoMi Smart Mirror Soon! <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The mirrors have computer processors and the mirrors can be used by shopping freaks to set up personal shopping accounts. <br/> <s> Now people can try clothes virtually, as a new development claims. The new development is related to <a>quot;smart mirrors<a>quot; which will allow people to try on clothes virtually. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The mirror has been created by MemoMi and apart from trying on clothes virtually, people can also change the colours of the garments digitally and share their choices with friends via email and social media platforms. The mirror even allows users record 7-second videos of themselves and compare which pair of jeans is suiting them the best. <br/> <s>The mirrors have computer processors and they can be used by shopping freaks to set up personal shopping accounts. The mirror lets them access their past purchase records and also the past trial videos from any personal device, virtually. Smart mirrors are the new future of shopping and the mirrors are already in use by Neiman Marcus in their department stores. This way the shopping experience will become more digital. Whenever the fitting sizes of any dress are available, the users are notified by the stores. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>The mirror is currently on trial and it will take some time before its worldwide launch. The device is also equipped by cameras and Intel hardware. MemoMi mirror interacts with users with help of an accompanying app on the smartphone or even by some simple body gestures. The smart mirror holds great potential for effective advertising too. <br/> <s>Reference: http://www.efytimes.com/e1/fullnews.asp?edid=158178'),
(257, '<iframe class="youtube" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/Hhgfz0zPmH4 "frameborder="0" allowfullscreen ></iframe><br/> The way in which we interact with the outside world has changed SO much since the introduction of the internet, smart phones, etc. In the very near future, another huge jump will be made: integrating the information on the internet with our surroundings. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>By that I mean being able to look at a building, product or place and immediately seeing information about the subject on our devices and eventually just with our eyes. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>If youâ€™re still confused as to what I mean, check out the earliest innovation of this concept, Goggles by Google. This app allows you to take a picture of whatever you are looking at and instantly receive info about it on your Android phone. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Like the video says, Goggle is only scratching at the surface of this technology. Kurzweil says that <a>quot;By 2020 we will routinely have pop ups in our visual field of view that give us background about the people and places that weâ€™re looking at.<a>quot; Your memory and the vast information bank of the internet will be one at all times.'),
(258, '<img src="uploads/mridula/projectnotesPic/2015-02-18_04:48:23am_Indian_Dark_Horse_Release_Image_highres.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;" onError="this.src="img/default.gif"" /><br/> Indian MotorcycleÂ®, Americaâ€™s first motorcycle company, on 13th Feb announced the newest and edgiest member of the Indian Chief line-up and the first 2016 model â€” the IndianÂ® Chief Dark HorseÂ®. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Based on the Indian Chief platform that relaunched the company two model years ago, the Dark Horse blacks out the bulk of the bike while only tossing in a few splashes of chrome. Note how the headlight nacelle and fork covers wear a semi-gloss black finish while the exhaust system and fender rails wear the most noticeable chrome on the motorcycle. Machining on the engineâ€™s cooling fins help it to stand out on the dark, hulking form. The Dark Horse differs from its progenitors in the use of cast aluminum wheels which serve to accentuate the aggressive stance of the bikeâ€™s silhouette. <br/> <s> <br/> <s><a>quot;The Indian Chief Dark Horse is unlike anything else currently available from Indian Motorcycle,<a>quot; said Indian Motorcycle Sr. Product Manager, Ben Lindaman. <a>quot;While it shares the best traits with other models in the Chief platform, its signature matte black paint and minimalist profile give it an attitude unlike any other Indian motorcycle. We are excited to unveil this new bike at an aggressive price point for a full-size cruiser.<a>quot; <br/> <s>The 2016 Indian Chief Dark Horse rolls into dealers mid-February. Daytona Bike Week attendees will be able to demo the Dark Horse from March 7thâ€“14th. <br/> <s> <br/> <s>Read more at: http://www.indianmotorcycle.com/en-us/stories/indian-dark-horse-press-release <br/> <s>http://www.ocregister.com/articles/new-651482-geneva-maserati.html <br/> <s><a>lt;iframe width=<a>quot;420<a>quot; height=<a>quot;315<a>quot; <br/> <s>src=<a>quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/GY3-A0EHXRo<a>quot;<a>gt; <br/> <s><a>lt;/i